,Recommended,265890,16366081,"Posted: 13 June, 2015",all,Aro,"I really enjoyed my time withHexcells, it's a simple but very challenging puzzle game that can keep you entertained for hours. It's often refered to as a twist on the old game called Minesweeper, and in a sense it is fairly similar, but more challenging and definitely much more satisfying to play with it's ambient theme and elegant graphics style.The rules are simple enough to understand after the first few puzzles, with some more rules and features being introduced as you progress. Clear the orange hexes to reveal the patterns underneath, numbers indicate the amount of surrounded hexes that are part of the pattern. Complete each of the puzzles making as few mistakes as possible so that you can progress through to the next set.There isn't much more to say about this game other than the fact that it is brilliant.Hexcellsis one of the best puzzle games I have played in recent years and I am really glad that I picked it up in the Steam Sale to give it a try, for such a cheap price, it's more than worth it. Would definitely recommend this to any puzzle fans of any age."
