,Recommended,265890,16622579,"Posted: 22 June, 2015",all,mouseas,"Reminds me a bit of Hex-Mines, a hexagonal version of classic Minesweeper. There aren't any mines (you lose points for guessing wrong, but you don't die), the levels are hand-built rather than randomly generated, and there are some very novel mechanics introduced with each group of levels.Pros:Good game mechanicsWell-made puzzles, all of which are solvable without guessworkCons:Few levels and no player-created or periodic content, and thus little replay value.Summary:If you like puzzle games, snag this on a sale for about $1. It'll last you about 2 hours.After looking around, it turns out the game has two sequels which expand on the game mechanics and add randomly-generated levels."
