,Recommended,265890,16518285,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,Kiefer,"Pros:- Based on classic Minesweeper, but more forgiving- All levels are solvable without guessing - lots of satisfaction when you complete one!- Nice atmosphere, albeit maybe distractingCons:- Becomes rather bland after a while- Quite shortI find Hexcells cute - it's basically an interesting iteration on classic Minesweeper. The basic mechanics are pretty much the same, the difference being that squares are now hexagons. It's also a lot more forgiving, although you'll likely find yourself restarting games just because you want to complete each level without any mistakes. Besides, all levels are solvable without guessing, and  completing a difficult level will often fill you with satisfaction. The atmosphere is quite enjoyable, although I found myself switching off the sound because it could be slightly distracting.However, there is some criticism to be made. Once you get the grip of the game mechanics, which should happen quite soon, the game becomes rather limited. The most challenging levels become a time for staring at the screen, wondering ""what am I missing?"". You'll often get stuck and resort to carefully scanning the screen, trying to find out which is the next tile you can click on. And that is why I'd game this game a mixed review if I could - it can become a test of patience rather than one of cleverness. Although fans of Minesweeper will not probably be bothered much. ;)The game is also quite short, considering that I beat all levels with a perfect score in just two hours. However, if you can get this one in a bundle or in an offer (I got it for 0.89 Euro), then it's likely that you'll have put your money to good use."
