,Recommended,265890,20312651,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Annavel,"I was expecting this game to be a minesweeper rip-off, but was pleasantly surprised to find that it's not. The basic mechanic is the same. Use the numbers on the hexes to determine which of the surrounding hexes are part of the pattern, rinse and repeat. Then the game throws in new ideas such as consecutive and nonadjacent hexes that force you to reconsider how you approach the problem. The last few puzzles are real mind-teasers! The best part is that there'sNO GUESSING INVOLVED. You can logic your way through every puzzle in this game. It's simple enough to get you hooked, but challenging enough to keep you invested. Too bad it's so short!"
