76561198012424039,Not Recommended,265890,23475556,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,11,"Hexcells is a nice simple little puzzle game, with the same relaxing gameplay as Minesweeper, and, it was entertaining for a while. I got the bundle on sale so it cost less than a candy bar, which is a good price for the 4 hours of fun I got out of it.However there are a couple gameplay aspects that I don’t like, and one game braking issue that has ruined the Hexcells for me, thus I can’t recommend it.I am going to compare Hexcells to Minesweeper in this review, I understand that it is not suppose to be the same game, but they are the only two games in this genre that I have experience with.First, lets look at the parts I like.Pros:The music is peaceful, and the sound effects fit in nicely.The game looks clean and modern.Unlike minesweeper, it is not stressful to click on tiles. (Though, this does have the effect of making it a little less satisfying when you complete the puzzle correctly.)I like the extra tile options {3} for three connected tiles, -2- for two disconnected tiles, and the numbers on the outside of the grid for tiles in that row or column.I like the fact that there is no timer, so I don’t feel rushed. (I hate puzzle games that make you rush)I also like that the levels are not too hard to unlock.Unfortunately that is as far as the pros go for me.Cons:Unlike minesweeper, it counts a mistake if you flag a number tile! This is frustrating, especially when there is no “think about it” flag.  It may help if tiles that have their conditions met grey out, even if I have to do this manually, it would help I think.There is not a “replay” button on screen.  This only became a problem when I started really trying to get perfect scores, which was pretty quickly.I could not swap the mouse buttons.  I don’t know why, but I couldn’t get the mouse buttons to register as “keys.” By default the flag and destroy buttons are opposite Minesweeper, which really really messed up my clicking!  And, because flagging counted as a mistake I couldn’t even have one safe button!  In the end, I had to use keyboard keys and even though it’s not so bad, the entire thing was really frustrating.And here is the game braking issue!There is a really really easy way to cheat!It is so easy that once you know it is there, you can’t help but use it to your advantage, even if only accidentally!Please, if you enjoy this puzzle game, and don’t know about this yet, don’t read below.YOU CAN SEE BEHIND YELLOW TILES!!!  As you mouse over yellow covered tiles they wiggle a little, and the yellow is just that, a cover, the tile is already there!  If the cover moves far enough you can see the tile color behind it, whether it is blue or black! Even if you don’t actively try to peek, just moving the mouse around like normal will give you glimpses.  This completely broke the game for me because what is the point of spending time working out hard tiles when I can just mouse over them a bunch to see if my guess is right!!!"
