76561198263633680,Recommended,265890,19517929,"Posted: 5 December, 2015",all,Lavnlvas2,"It's Minesweeper with some additional elements that change the way you have to think about the feild of play -- Nothing wrong with that.But, in Minesweeper, when you hit a mine, you lose. Here, you have a mistakes counter and no easy way of resetting. So, if you screw up, it doesn't matter. I found myself getting more frustrated at the fact that I had to return to the menu, rather than simply hit a reset. There's an acheivement for getting through with no mistakes, but that didn't feel like it added much.There are not an over abundance of levels, which is a shame, becasue it was fun enough to play. I saw in the news that thereis an editor to make fan levels. I'm sure it is a grab bag.I would have loved to see an infinite or random level generator, but i'm sure that would be much more difficult than a standard minesweeper level generator, simply because of the new mechanics added."
