,Recommended,265890,17891537,"Posted: 5 September, 2015",all,LonM,"Hexels is a nice puzzle game that plays on number and logic puzzles in a style that seems reminiscent of minesweeper, but on a hexagonl grid.The puzzles themselves are for the most part solvable by logic. The only one that had me completely stumped as to how to start it was puzzle 6.2. This game is only worth getting if you want to exercise your understanding of logic, however. As the puzzles are not generated randomly, you could just look up the solutions online, or click randomly to beat them.The music in this game is very nice, and is pretty ""zen"".The graphics are very nice and minimalist, however there is a glaring bug in the game. When you hover over cells, they ""wiggle"". This is a nice addition, however sometimes the wiggle is enough to let you see what is underneath, which ruins the point of using logic. A solution to this is to use flux to remove the blue colour from your screen, but that is points against the game. If you don't have flux, try and avoid hovering over the cells to much.The game only took me about 2 hours to complete, so it's fairly short, but if you want something to exercise logic, then this is a good game to play."
