,Recommended,265890,18068805,"Posted: 17 September, 2015",all,vianmeor,"This is an easy recommendation to make! YES!Hexcells is a puzzle game that's sort of like Minesweeper, but with more unique twists (many more rulings to make it a bit more complex). It's a frustrating game in the sense that you feel that you should be able to solve it, and making mistakes disappoints you more than you'd think (especially if you're after the Achievements - but even then, it keeps count how many mistakes you've made so far and displays it for the whole level, which stings). At some point, you'll likely get frustrated when you dont know what move to make - but you know that (and I can confirm that) there is always a 'legal' or 'smart' move (meaning it's assured correct; no need to have to guess to proceed).For those after the Achievements, this is a (relatively) quick game to go for - four hours and a bit for me to complete, counting restarts when mistakes are made (but I'm a puzzle afficionado so I might have ate through it a bit faster than average) and a noteworthy detail is that you dont feel like you're achievement hunting (as in doing obscure actions for the achievement) so much as just playing the game to its full.At this price? It's an easy buy - but getting it on sale, more especially on the complete pack?The game is more than worth the price!As an aside, even if the levels are the same, there is replayability in that the field is just so expansive and keeping track of all the minute details is near impossible.Get this game! The developers did a really good job with it!"
