,Recommended,265890,11954308,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,Andara Bledin,"I bought Hexcells on sale because it was $1.01, and the gameplay looked like precisely the sort of thing I would enjoy as a fan of both Minesweeper and Betrapped!The preview images and videos tell you all you need to know about how to play the game. The rules are simple, and the premise is a fresh take on the Minesweeper gameplay with another layer of complexity for those of us who like a bit more challenge in our logic puzzles.I was not disappointed. But, had I paid full price, I would have found the shortness of the game (I completed it with perfection in 70 minutes) and the static nature of the puzzles to be offputting.Ultimately, I can't recommend this game at full price unless you are a major fan of the genre, but at the sale price, it's a buck well spent. Hopefully the upcoming Hexcells Infinite will offer a more extended play opportunity.Pros - Clear in-game instructions. Excellent concept and implementation. Pleasant ambiant music.Cons - A finite number of puzzles. No 'free play' mode or randomized puzzles, so no replay value. A bit on the short side."
