,Recommended,265890,13440460,"Posted: 18 December, 2014",all,Gunstable,"If you ever liked Minesweeper you will love Hexcells! It's played on a hex grid, but has a similar mechanic of combining information to deduce the locations of the blue hexes (mines). The information you get is more diverse than Minesweeper.What is especially noteworthy here is the outstanding level design. The game consists of 35 or so levels that gradually escalate in difficulty, while never requiring the player to outright guess. I repeat: Every puzzle can be logically deduced with the information available. I recommend playing it without guessing, since figuring out the logical deductions is immensely rewarding.The two sequel games (Hexcells Plus, Hexcells Infinite) have the same mechanic but additional levels. Hexcells Infinite also has randomly-generated levels in addition to the hand-crafted ones. All three are fantastic games that any puzzle lover will enjoy!"
