76561198045892908,Recommended,265890,19929002,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,Tyepo76,"Ok, for a seemingly simple looking puzzle game, this one is surprisingly addictive.  It feels kind of like minesweeper, but with different ways of visualizing the pattern instead of just the number of ""mines"" surrounding a block.  Best of all, I have not had to guess once yet and I have beaten Hexcells, and am halfway through Hexcells Plus.  It does get challenging, but the solution can still be figured out using logic.  My wife even enjoys this game quite a bit, and she doesn't play games often.My main gripe with this game is that the controls feel backwards from minesweeper in that you left click the block that is part of the pattern (a mine), and right click an empty block.  I have played a good bit of minesweeper in the past and right click for mine and left click for empty was a very hard habit to break.  I had to restart many puzzles due to click confusion.  Unfortunately the game doesn't make you restart when you make a mistake, but it does keep track of the number of mistakes.  If you want to go for the perfectionist achievement, you have to beat every level without mistakes, and it doesn't seem to tell you which levels you made mistakes on if you choose to complete the stage with mistakes.  I get around this problem by restarting the level when I make a mistake.Overall, this is a great addition to the library!"
