,Recommended,265890,11969490,"Posted: 3 September, 2014",all,castorquinn,"Gorgeously simple.  Clean and elegant to look at, Hexcells plays like a cross between minesweeper and sudoku; in fact the feel of Hexcells is so similar to those style of puzzles that anyone who likes them will like this.  It won't take long to scoot through the game, but the puzzles are genuinely enjoyable and in the later levels you can spend a good few minutes stalled, hunting for the clue you've missed and deciding whether or not to just take a punt and click a tile.  In fact that's the best thing about this game: unlike minesweeper and many sudoku, you don't at any point need to guess; the entire solution is workable from the initial position of the tiles.  So if you don't get it ... well, it's on you.  If you can pick this up for a few dollars, it is definitely worth the time."
