76561198025619129,Recommended,265890,18820374,"Posted: 1 November, 2015",all,Micawber,"Hexcells is a delightful little puzzle game, a bit like minesweeper but much more interesting and well-built. Unlike Minesweeper, you never need to guess in Hexcells - using the hints provided at the beginning of the level, you can work your way to a completed field using logic alone. If you're a fan of sudoku or Minesweeper, I can guarantee you'll enjoy this game.As the first game in the series, it lacks a bit of the polish of later entries (saving partially completed puzzles isn't added until the third installment) and it's a little to easy to get to the end (I got perfect on all stages in less than four hours taking my time), but it serves as a great introduction to the much more challenging later games. I reccomend picking up all three games on sale as I did - the difficulty scales is such a way that it feels like playing through one larger game.Overall, a really refreshing, if somewhat easy, puzzle game. Grab the sequels if you want more polish and challenge."
