76561198171827793,Recommended,265890,14685382,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,FreyaQ,"I bought this short but sweet game when it was on sale for 50 cents. I didn't expect much, so it was a pleasant surprise to find a true logic game.Though Hexcells borrows elements from several different puzzle games, I was most reminded of nonograms, also known as Picross or Hanjie, which I've solved hundreds of by hand and in video games. As with nonograms, the game's beauty lies in the fact that the rules are are simple and it is purely logic-based (instead of relying on gimmicks or time-limits). That means that even in the later puzzles, which can be a bit challenging, you never have to resort to guess-work and anyone can solve them easily with enough focus and time.It's true the game was far too short (you can get 100% completion in a few hours), but now that I've tried it I would recommend it even at full price, though of course preferably wait for a sale. Apparently, the third installment has a random puzzle generator, which soundss like exactly the kind of thing this kind of game needs, but I will have to try it to see. Regardless, this game has proven the concept amazingly well and given my brains a few solid hours of work to do for the price of a cup of coffee."
