,Recommended,265890,20668942,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,Note,"Hexcells is a really nice spin on the classic minesweeper we all know (and love).. Instead of clearing out squares, you now have to clear hexagons, which surprisingly creates new challenges to overcome. Things get even more interesting once new mechanics are thrown into the mix like a certain amount of marked hexagons being next to each other or having at least one gap in between marked hexagons. They're added overtime, just so the player can get comfortable with the new skills they're learning though the previous levels. If you're hungry for a new kind of minesweeper, complete with an ambient soundtrack, a smooth difficulty curve, and a whole lotta hexagons, you can't go wrong with Hexcells...I do warn you that the game might feel a bit short, but hey, that's what Hexcells Infinite is for.. OUO"
