76561198030812107,Recommended,265890,23851504,"Posted: 26 June, 2016",all,Allan,"As any review can tell you, this starts out as Minesweeper on hexagons. Later levels introduce interesting twists, like rules about adjacency and totals for columns of hexes. Puzzles range from trivial in the beginning to vast and complex in the end.My only real complaint is that the game is short; it's just 30 levels, and much of that is spent ramping up through puzzles that hew to the easy side. All in all I spent just 100 minutes clearing Hexcells. Still, for just 90 cents I do feel like I got good value for this purchase."
