,Recommended,265890,34079957,Posted: 7 August,all,MurrayL,"A fantastic little puzzle game with a novel twist on the Minesweeper formula. Hexcells isn't big, but it is clever. As the game goes on, it adds several layers of complexity to what is initially a simple concept, and things get very challenging by the end.The sound and music are also worthy of note, being minimalist but lovely. I never got tired of how the reveal sounds synced up to the music.The only downside - and a small one at that - is that you can 'cheat' by flicking the mouse quickly over a hex and seeing a glimpse of the colour underneath. This is easy enough to do by accident, revealing a hex that you hadn't worked out yet and spoiling part of the puzzle."
