76561198144594439,Recommended,265890,34262926,Posted: 15 August,all,Ambient Tea,"i really like this easy but creative and estheticly pleasing spin on the classic minesweeper.aside from the game being played on a hex board of a different shape each level, later stages introduce some variations to the rules: mine counts per row/column, consecutive counts etc. what i really appreciated is that unlike original minesweeper, there is no guesing necessary - the levels are crafted so that there is always enough information to make a correct move.the ambient, soothing soundtrack is also certainly a plus. the game overall does a good job to make the player relaxed.also - prefect playthrough took me a little more than 6 hours, which is reasonable for this price."
