,Recommended,265890,35477936,Posted: 4 October,all,MCLJN,"I don't understand the people saying ""It's just like minesweeper if you like minesweeper you'll like this...""The only way that this game is like minesweeper is that you reveal what is beneath hidden tiles. That is where the similarity ends.If you make a mistake in the game, it is entirely your fault. There is no luck. Its all about pure logic. If you play this game without caring wether or not you make a mistake, then you are turning it into a different game altogether and not playing it as intended. Another user's ridiculous comment on his negative review ""there is no penalty for making a mistake."" The penalty is the mistake itself and it makes perfect sense for this game.All that said, this game is fantastic. This is easily my favorite 2D puzzle game. The sequels only get better. Go buy this and its sequels."
